Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of painted rock art showing four human figures and three unidentified shapes in dark brown pigment. The human figures are all upright and faded/rudimentary so impossible to tell which direction they face. They are all heavily segmented with torso head and arms, legs, and feet represented as discrete portions, infilled. Three such figures stand in a row at bottom left, with the tallest to the right of them. To the left of this tall figure is a vertical unidentified object with a thin looped outline in the same pigment. Above this is an unidentified shape and to the far right of the image are two dark infilled vertical bars in parallel. A 5cm scale bar has been fitted at the bottom of the image. Wadi Anak, Egypt. Scanned
Curator's comments: This site is a long, sloping shelter running up and under the protected side of an inselberg.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
